1
00:00:12,817 --> 00:00:16,400
[KAZUKI]
Toi!

2
00:00:36,150 --> 00:00:38,400
Where am I?

3
00:00:38,483 --> 00:00:40,567
Just think of it as the past.

4
00:00:40,650 --> 00:00:44,692
Specifically, right after those
little traitors screwed us over.

5
00:00:45,858 --> 00:00:47,817
The outside of
the circle is this way,

6
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,150
but it's down much,
much further.

7
00:00:50,233 --> 00:00:53,733
A place with no connections,
no beginning and no end.

8
00:00:53,817 --> 00:00:55,150
And that means
you have to give up

9
00:00:55,233 --> 00:00:57,358
your connections to get there.

10
00:00:57,442 --> 00:01:00,483
Is it really that easy?

11
00:01:00,567 --> 00:01:02,067
[CHIKAI]
Of course.

12
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:04,942
Just shoot the Toi of the past.

13
00:01:05,025 --> 00:01:07,358
All you need
is that gun of yours.

14
00:01:29,025 --> 00:01:31,525
[KAZUKI grunts, gasps]

15
00:01:31,608 --> 00:01:33,067
What is this place?

16
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,775
[KEPPI]
It's Toi's past.

17
00:01:34,858 --> 00:01:36,692
I presume he's
erasing it bit by bit

18
00:01:36,775 --> 00:01:38,483
as he travels
outside the circle.

19
00:01:38,567 --> 00:01:40,317
--[BOTH gasp]
--[KEPPI] If he succeeds,

20
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:43,192
not only will he will erase
his connection to you,

21
00:01:43,275 --> 00:01:45,150
but his existence as well.

22
00:01:45,233 --> 00:01:47,317
I won't let him do that.

23
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:50,442
[gunshot]

24
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:54,983
[gunshot]

25
00:01:58,233 --> 00:02:00,358
[gunshot]

26
00:02:02,942 --> 00:02:06,025
[CHIKAI] Nice work.
Way to wipe it all out.

27
00:02:06,108 --> 00:02:07,233
It can't hurt you anymore

28
00:02:07,317 --> 00:02:10,067
if it never happened
to begin with, right?

29
00:02:13,608 --> 00:02:15,483
[KAZUKI]
We got here too late.

30
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:18,400
Then what's next?
Where would he be going?

31
00:02:19,608 --> 00:02:22,067
--Four years back.
--[ENTA gasps]

32
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:23,483
Just think.

33
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:25,567
If Toi really wants to break
his connection to us,

34
00:02:25,650 --> 00:02:27,483
that's the place.

35
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:31,608
That day, when we first met
and he gave me the <i>miçanga</i> .

36
00:02:31,692 --> 00:02:33,067
[ENTA]
I see.

37
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:35,650
--You remember after all.
--[KAZUKI] Yeah.

38
00:02:35,733 --> 00:02:37,858
That really was
the start of everything.

39
00:02:37,942 --> 00:02:39,192
If it wasn't for that <i>miçanga</i> ,

40
00:02:39,275 --> 00:02:40,775
who knows how things
would've turned out for us.

41
00:02:40,858 --> 00:02:42,608
The <i>miçanga</i> hasn't disappeared,

42
00:02:42,692 --> 00:02:44,775
so we still have time
to stop him.

43
00:02:46,192 --> 00:02:48,483
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Who invited you?

44
00:02:48,567 --> 00:02:51,442
Get "otter" here,
you poison-spewing pests!

45
00:02:51,525 --> 00:02:54,192
--[gushing]
--[BOTH yelling]

46
00:02:58,275 --> 00:03:00,358
[KEPPI]
Oh, no! [farts]

47
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,025
[BOTH]
Keppi!

48
00:03:05,108 --> 00:03:07,025
[KEPPI] I shall try my best
to buy you some time.

49
00:03:07,108 --> 00:03:10,983
Carry on without me!
I have faith in you!

50
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:13,525
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
My goodness. You stayed behind

51
00:03:13,608 --> 00:03:16,025
in "otter" to let
the rats escape?

52
00:03:16,108 --> 00:03:19,358
You must have a death wish.

53
00:03:19,442 --> 00:03:21,608
You've had your way
for far too long.

54
00:03:21,692 --> 00:03:24,525
We're going to settle this
right here and right now, Otter.

55
00:03:24,608 --> 00:03:27,275
[IMPERIAL BOSS] Are you sure
it was your despair you cut out

56
00:03:27,358 --> 00:03:29,317
and not your common sense?

57
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:33,525
As if I would lose to someone
as diminished as you.

58
00:03:33,608 --> 00:03:36,317
I've already filled you
with despair once.

59
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,900
If you're so eager for me
to do it again,

60
00:03:38,983 --> 00:03:41,400
I'll oblige!

61
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:49,358
This is it. Where it all began.

62
00:03:51,692 --> 00:03:53,650
That's right.

63
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:57,900
Now put a bullet in little you
and your connection is gone.

64
00:03:57,983 --> 00:04:06,025
After that, you'll be
outside the circle.

65
00:04:06,108 --> 00:04:08,233
[TOI] I wanted to
play soccer.

66
00:04:08,317 --> 00:04:10,650
I wanted to go pro.

67
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:13,650
I had my mom, my dad,
and my brother with me.

68
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:16,233
I thought I could do anything.

69
00:04:16,317 --> 00:04:18,650
That everything
would work out fine.

70
00:04:18,733 --> 00:04:20,400
Too bad.

71
00:04:20,483 --> 00:04:22,650
Mom and Dad left us behind,

72
00:04:22,733 --> 00:04:24,983
and their poor boy
shot a man dead.

73
00:04:25,067 --> 00:04:26,442
[gunshot]

74
00:04:29,067 --> 00:04:32,817
[TOI] But even after
all that, I wasn't alone.

75
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:35,358
My brother was
still there for me.

76
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:39,192
Yeah, right.
You really believe that?

77
00:04:39,275 --> 00:04:44,233
I'm a bad guy, after all.
Obviously, I was just using you.

78
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:47,150
[TOI]
Still, I was fine with that.

79
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:49,275
I'd throw anything away.

80
00:04:49,358 --> 00:04:52,858
Do anything.
Whatever it took.

81
00:04:55,525 --> 00:04:56,983
What's wrong?

82
00:04:57,067 --> 00:04:58,567
Still clinging to
those connections,

83
00:04:58,650 --> 00:05:01,400
after you've come so far?

84
00:05:01,483 --> 00:05:04,150
I made this connection
on my own.

85
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:06,525
I don't need you here to end it.

86
00:05:06,608 --> 00:05:08,192
[gunshot]

87
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:16,525
Hmm. Bad guys are the ones
who survive in this world.

88
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:21,983
--Remember that.
--[IMPERIAL BOSS] Otterly.

89
00:05:22,817 --> 00:05:25,775
[TOI]
Goodbye, brother.

90
00:05:26,275 --> 00:05:30,650
Now, finally,
I can bring this to an end.

91
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:32,608
[gunshot]

92
00:05:36,483 --> 00:05:39,233
--[yells]
--[clattering]

93
00:05:39,317 --> 00:05:40,900
Kazuki!
[grunts]

94
00:05:42,775 --> 00:05:44,358
[TOI]
Why are you here?

95
00:05:44,442 --> 00:05:46,817
[KAZUKI]
To take you back.

96
00:05:49,567 --> 00:05:52,483
I'm sick of you both. Go away!

97
00:05:53,650 --> 00:05:54,733
[gunshot]

98
00:05:54,817 --> 00:05:57,817
[gasps]

99
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,567
The <i>miçanga</i> !

100
00:05:59,650 --> 00:06:01,942
[DARK KEPPI]
Dadadadadadadadadadadada.

101
00:06:02,025 --> 00:06:03,817
Darkness!

102
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:07,858
[ENTA] Dark Keppi.
Damn it, he tricked us!

103
00:06:07,942 --> 00:06:09,858
Toi.

104
00:06:09,942 --> 00:06:12,442
[grunting]

105
00:06:12,525 --> 00:06:15,192
[KAZUKI] I won't give up
on our connection.

106
00:06:15,275 --> 00:06:17,108
No matter what.

107
00:06:17,192 --> 00:06:19,817
Even if you cut me off,

108
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,817
I'll connect again and again!

109
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:23,608
[gasps]

110
00:06:25,858 --> 00:06:29,233
[DARK KEPPI]
Dadadadadadadadadada.

111
00:06:29,317 --> 00:06:31,067
Da-Darkness.

112
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:33,983
Erase all connections
from your memory!

113
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:44,275
[gasps]

114
00:06:44,358 --> 00:06:46,817
We're falling? What now?

115
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:49,942
[gasps]
What's that thing?

116
00:06:59,525 --> 00:07:02,442
[ALL yelling]

117
00:07:04,067 --> 00:07:05,900
[KAZUKI]
I know what's it's like.

118
00:07:05,983 --> 00:07:08,650
I wanted to leave
this world, too.

119
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,942
I wasn't connected to anything.

120
00:07:11,025 --> 00:07:14,442
I didn't belong here.

121
00:07:14,525 --> 00:07:16,150
But deep down,

122
00:07:16,233 --> 00:07:18,442
I think I was
waiting for someone.

123
00:07:18,525 --> 00:07:20,483
For a hand to reach out.

124
00:07:20,567 --> 00:07:23,525
A friend to tell me
I was being stubborn.

125
00:07:23,608 --> 00:07:28,108
Then, suddenly,
I found a way to smile again.

126
00:07:28,192 --> 00:07:32,442
I can't lose our connection.
Not after all this.

127
00:07:32,525 --> 00:07:36,733
I can feel it.
Our memories are fading away!

128
00:07:37,942 --> 00:07:40,358
We have to stop this!

129
00:07:40,442 --> 00:07:42,650
[ALL yelling]

130
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,192
[ENTA]
I know what it's like.

131
00:07:45,275 --> 00:07:47,858
I wanted to leave
this world, too.

132
00:07:47,942 --> 00:07:49,775
I've always watched
from a distance,

133
00:07:49,858 --> 00:07:52,692
a coward, lost
in my own reality.

134
00:07:52,775 --> 00:07:54,108
But deep down,

135
00:07:54,192 --> 00:07:56,733
I think I was waiting
for someone.

136
00:07:56,817 --> 00:07:59,358
A hand to pull me out
of all my hopeless fantasies

137
00:07:59,442 --> 00:08:01,942
and into the real world.

138
00:08:02,025 --> 00:08:03,567
I don't know when to quit.

139
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,692
So I'm not letting
go of anything.

140
00:08:05,775 --> 00:08:09,192
Not a single one of these
smiles that we fought for.

141
00:08:11,692 --> 00:08:14,317
Damn it!
It's all slipping away!

142
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,442
We can't give up now!

143
00:08:16,525 --> 00:08:18,692
[ALL yelling]

144
00:08:20,192 --> 00:08:24,442
[TOI] For a long time now,
I've wanted to leave this world.

145
00:08:24,525 --> 00:08:27,650
I wasn't given the chance
to laugh or cry anymore,

146
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:30,400
and eventually I lost hope.

147
00:08:30,483 --> 00:08:32,900
Deep down,
I think I was waiting.

148
00:08:32,983 --> 00:08:37,275
For a bullet in the head to
free me from this life of crime.

149
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,067
[TOI]
And yet...

150
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:44,983
...even though I was sure there
was no place left for me...

151
00:08:45,067 --> 00:08:48,858
Even though I was sure
I could throw everything away.

152
00:08:50,108 --> 00:08:51,692
Stop it!

153
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,025
I can't lose you now.

154
00:08:57,692 --> 00:08:59,733
Kazuki. Enta.

155
00:09:01,317 --> 00:09:04,233
I've thrown enough away already!

156
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,942
No more!

157
00:09:10,233 --> 00:09:12,692
Sara!

158
00:09:12,775 --> 00:09:13,942
[BOTH]
Sara!

159
00:09:14,025 --> 00:09:18,067
[ALL]
Sara!

160
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:20,692
Sarazanmai!

161
00:09:20,775 --> 00:09:22,442
[KEPPI]
<i>Kero</i> !

162
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:28,567
--[KEPPI grunts]
--[KAZUKI] All right!

163
00:09:28,650 --> 00:09:31,733
--[ENTA] Kazuki!
--Okay, but what now?

164
00:09:31,817 --> 00:09:35,567
[KAZUKI] We still have
this <i>miçanga</i> . That's enough.

165
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:37,442
[KEPPI grunts]

166
00:09:37,983 --> 00:09:40,692
[KAZUKI] We just need to
give it to me four years ago.

167
00:09:43,983 --> 00:09:45,108
[cracking]

168
00:09:45,192 --> 00:09:46,067
[BOTH gasp]

169
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:50,817
[DARK KEPPI]
Dadadadadadadada.

170
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:53,525
Darkness!

171
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,900
[KEPPI] The time has come.
It seems I must

172
00:09:56,983 --> 00:09:59,733
face my despair,
just like you brave souls.

173
00:09:59,817 --> 00:10:03,775
This will be
the final Sarazanmai.

174
00:10:14,108 --> 00:10:16,650
[ALL 3] ♪ Time to take back
what I need ♪

175
00:10:16,733 --> 00:10:19,192
♪ I can't leave
'til I retrieve it ♪

176
00:10:19,275 --> 00:10:20,233
♪ Our connection! ♪

177
00:10:20,317 --> 00:10:21,733
♪ It hides a secret
that I must ♪

178
00:10:21,817 --> 00:10:24,733
♪ let everybody see ♪

179
00:10:24,817 --> 00:10:27,317
♪ Time to take back
what I need ♪

180
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:30,025
♪ I can't leave
'til I retrieve it ♪

181
00:10:30,108 --> 00:10:31,900
♪ Our connection!
Precious secrets ♪

182
00:10:31,983 --> 00:10:34,275
--♪ hiding in our history ♪
--[DARK KEPPI] Dadadadadadadada.

183
00:10:34,358 --> 00:10:36,025
[ALL 3]
♪ Set them free ♪

184
00:10:36,108 --> 00:10:37,733
♪ Carry on through! ♪

185
00:10:37,817 --> 00:10:41,275
[ALL 3]
♪ How can I connect to you? ♪

186
00:10:41,358 --> 00:10:46,317
♪ Share your love,
with a heart that's ever true ♪

187
00:10:46,733 --> 00:10:51,733
[IMPERIAL BOSS] ♪ Deep inside,
I exist conceptually ♪

188
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:55,442
♪ Reflecting desire "otterly" ♪

189
00:10:55,525 --> 00:10:57,108
[ALL 3 gasp]

190
00:10:57,192 --> 00:10:59,942
[ALL]
♪ You can't stop me! ♪

191
00:11:00,025 --> 00:11:02,692
[ALL 3] ♪ Burning hearts,
enter the fray ♪

192
00:11:02,775 --> 00:11:05,317
--♪ Embrace the truth... ♪
--Nailed it!

193
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,567
♪ This is love ♪

194
00:11:06,650 --> 00:11:10,692
♪ I can say,
because I feel it from you ♪

195
00:11:10,775 --> 00:11:12,900
♪ Souls combine
stack up the plates ♪

196
00:11:12,983 --> 00:11:14,400
--Nailed it!
--♪ Mystic ball ♪

197
00:11:14,483 --> 00:11:15,650
♪ deciding our fates ♪

198
00:11:15,733 --> 00:11:18,233
♪ Our wishes ♪

199
00:11:18,317 --> 00:11:21,400
--♪ Our dishes ♪
--[KEPPI yelling]

200
00:11:21,483 --> 00:11:23,567
♪ Sarazanmai! ♪

201
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:24,858
[DARK KEPPI grunts]

202
00:11:24,942 --> 00:11:28,192
[KEPPI]
I have captured my desire.

203
00:11:30,025 --> 00:11:31,692
Almost there!

204
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:35,900
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
Forgetting someone?

205
00:11:38,858 --> 00:11:41,067
Damn it! I can't see a thing!

206
00:11:51,983 --> 00:11:55,400
--Let desire flow!
--Never let it go!

207
00:12:11,275 --> 00:12:12,733
Almost there!

208
00:12:12,817 --> 00:12:14,733
Let's...

209
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:22,400
...go!

210
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:32,483
[KEPPI]
We're connected!

211
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:35,692
[IMPERIAL BOSS]
I am Otter.

212
00:12:35,775 --> 00:12:38,650
I am a concept.

213
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:40,608
I cannot die.

214
00:12:40,692 --> 00:12:44,067
[slowing]
You "otter" believe it.

215
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:52,150
The time has come at last!
Traverse it!

216
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:55,150
The River of Desire calls you!

217
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:18,192
[ALL 3 yelling]

218
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:23,775
[MALE VOICE]
The future is leaking!

219
00:13:23,858 --> 00:13:25,400
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

220
00:13:25,483 --> 00:13:27,858
[TOI]
But we're out of time!

221
00:13:27,942 --> 00:13:31,150
[ENTA] If we don't make
this pass, we're done for!

222
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:34,650
[KAZUKI] This goal is mine!
I want to take it!

223
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:36,567
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

224
00:13:39,233 --> 00:13:41,442
[KAZUKI]
But at this rate,

225
00:13:41,525 --> 00:13:43,192
it's not meant to be.

226
00:13:44,483 --> 00:13:46,442
[CROWD cheering]

227
00:13:46,525 --> 00:13:49,108
[beeping]

228
00:13:49,192 --> 00:13:51,150
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

229
00:13:54,275 --> 00:13:56,692
[TOI]
But I can't be forgiven.

230
00:13:56,775 --> 00:13:59,108
[CROWD cheering]

231
00:13:59,192 --> 00:14:01,108
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

232
00:14:04,275 --> 00:14:06,025
[ENTA]
But if nothing changes,

233
00:14:06,108 --> 00:14:08,692
I'm afraid
we'll never meet again.

234
00:14:08,775 --> 00:14:11,650
[CROWD cheering]

235
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:13,692
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

236
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:21,400
[KAZUKI] But when I try to
tell them my feelings...

237
00:14:21,483 --> 00:14:22,317
...I lie.

238
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,108
[CROWD cheering]

239
00:14:25,192 --> 00:14:28,442
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

240
00:14:28,525 --> 00:14:32,192
[TOI] But if I think
you'll throw me away...

241
00:14:32,275 --> 00:14:34,275
...I'll betray you.

242
00:14:34,358 --> 00:14:36,192
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

243
00:14:37,525 --> 00:14:40,900
[ENTA]
But it's too late now. I can't.

244
00:14:43,108 --> 00:14:44,400
[ENTA]
I can't express it.

245
00:14:44,483 --> 00:14:48,150
[TOI] It just feels like
you're all so far away.

246
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:50,733
[ALL 3]
I want to connect.

247
00:14:50,817 --> 00:14:53,525
[KAZUKI]
So I'm not giving up!

248
00:14:53,608 --> 00:14:56,025
[CROWD cheering]

249
00:14:56,108 --> 00:14:57,442
[ENTA grunts]

250
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:04,608
I've had enough, okay?

251
00:15:09,358 --> 00:15:11,317
I'm done with both of you!

252
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:19,067
[KAZUKI grunts]

253
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:25,650
It's over! Just go away!

254
00:15:31,483 --> 00:15:33,650
--[KAZUKI] Even then...
--[ENTA] Even then...

255
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:35,442
[TOI]
Even then...

256
00:15:35,525 --> 00:15:38,108
[ALL 3]
Even then, I still...

257
00:15:40,483 --> 00:15:42,983
[SARA]
The dish is the vessel of life.

258
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:47,983
So long as it has form, someday,
it will wear down and break.

259
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:52,025
What they saw was not
the future. It was the past.

260
00:15:52,108 --> 00:15:56,858
A future that could
have been a possibility.

261
00:15:56,942 --> 00:16:00,733
[KEPPI] The great circle of
this world was preserved today.

262
00:16:00,817 --> 00:16:03,442
And although the
future is ensured,

263
00:16:03,525 --> 00:16:05,817
it is not necessarily
a bright one.

264
00:16:08,692 --> 00:16:10,483
Thus is life.

265
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:13,942
Where hope and despair
walk ever hand-in-hand.

266
00:16:19,525 --> 00:16:20,942
[gasps]

267
00:16:21,025 --> 00:16:24,067
It's the Little Prince
and a princess, too!

268
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,900
[SARA]
You must never forget.

269
00:16:25,983 --> 00:16:29,567
The future of this world
can only be claimed

270
00:16:29,650 --> 00:16:32,358
by those who connect
their desires

271
00:16:32,442 --> 00:16:35,025
through their shared
pain of loss.

272
00:16:35,108 --> 00:16:39,483
[HARUKA] I get it.
It's my future to choose.

273
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:43,442
I'm gonna believe in that
and believe in my friends.

274
00:16:43,525 --> 00:16:45,942
Because I care about them.

275
00:16:46,025 --> 00:16:49,358
Sometimes I'm happy
and sometimes I'm sad.

276
00:16:49,442 --> 00:16:51,733
But I know they feel
the same way.

277
00:16:51,817 --> 00:16:54,025
That's why we're connected.

278
00:18:33,108 --> 00:18:35,358
[MALE OFFICER] Don't come
back here again, all right?

279
00:18:35,442 --> 00:18:38,817
You have a new life, kid,
and it begins now.

280
00:19:01,775 --> 00:19:04,608
[TOI] This world is built
upon connections.

281
00:19:06,192 --> 00:19:07,983
[TOI]
People share blood,

282
00:19:08,067 --> 00:19:11,650
the city they live in,
even their desires.

283
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,858
Lucky to be a froggy!

284
00:19:13,942 --> 00:19:17,608
Froggies are always lucky!
You'll be "hoppy" every day!

285
00:19:19,233 --> 00:19:21,567
[TOI]
Everyone is connected somehow.

286
00:19:24,942 --> 00:19:28,108
But everything in my life
has already ended.

287
00:19:28,192 --> 00:19:31,150
I can't get back what I've lost.

288
00:19:39,775 --> 00:19:42,067
[TOI]
Who the hell cares?

289
00:19:57,817 --> 00:20:02,108
[KAZUKI] ♪ Time to take back
what I need ♪

290
00:20:02,192 --> 00:20:06,317
♪ I can't leave
'til I retrieve it ♪

291
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:07,733
[ENTA]
♪ Our connection! ♪

292
00:20:07,817 --> 00:20:12,858
[KAZUKI] ♪ Precious secrets
hiding in our history ♪

293
00:20:12,942 --> 00:20:16,775
[ENTA]
♪ Set them free ♪

294
00:20:18,025 --> 00:20:19,442
[gasps]

295
00:20:24,150 --> 00:20:26,192
[gasps]
Welcome back, Toi!

296
00:20:26,275 --> 00:20:28,025
[gasps] We've been waiting!

297
00:20:28,108 --> 00:20:29,150
[TOI]
Why are you here?

298
00:20:29,233 --> 00:20:30,733
--Huh?
--Oh?

299
00:20:30,817 --> 00:20:33,150
Don't you realize
I'm sick of you two?

300
00:20:40,067 --> 00:20:42,483
[ALL 3]
♪ Sing our song every day ♪

301
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:45,275
♪ A miracle, moments away ♪

302
00:20:45,358 --> 00:20:47,442
♪ Hand in hand, come what may ♪

303
00:20:47,525 --> 00:20:50,483
♪ We're ready for tomorrow ♪

304
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:53,150
♪ Souls combine,
stack up the plates ♪

305
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:55,650
♪ Mystic ball,
deciding our fates ♪

306
00:20:55,733 --> 00:20:58,233
♪ Our wishes ♪

307
00:20:58,317 --> 00:21:02,108
♪ Our dishes ♪

308
00:21:02,192 --> 00:21:03,192
Sara!

309
00:21:03,275 --> 00:21:04,400
[BOTH]
Sara!

310
00:21:04,483 --> 00:21:09,900
[ALL 3]
Sara!

311
00:21:09,983 --> 00:21:11,900
Sarazanmai!

312
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:47,942
[boat horn honks]

